## Academic References

Core models implemented in this software are based on:

- Hodgkin, A. L., & Huxley, A. F. (1952). A quantitative description of membrane current and its application to conduction and excitation in nerve. The Journal of Physiology, 117(4), 500.

- FitzHugh, R. (1961). Impulses and physiological states in theoretical models of nerve membrane. Biophysical Journal, 1(6), 445-466.

- Corrias, A., & Buist, M. L. (2007). A quantitative model of gastric smooth muscle cellular activation. Annals of Biomedical Engineering, 35(9), 1595-1607.

- Raissi, M., Perdikaris, P., & Karniadakis, G. E. (2019). Physics-informed neural networks: A deep learning framework for solving forward and inverse problems involving nonlinear partial differential equations. Journal of Computational Physics, 378, 686-707.

Please cite these foundational works in addition to this software.
